Email Header Analysis – Sample 5

Subject: Bank Security Alert
Sender: security@bank-alerts.net

Findings:

Sender Domain:
bank-alerts.net

Indicators:

• Sender domain does not correspond to any known banking institution
• Generic greeting ("Dear Customer")
• Fear-based language suggesting account restriction
• Immediate verification request
• Suspicious external verification link

Authentication Indicators (Expected):

SPF: Fail or Unknown
DKIM: Not present
DMARC: Fail

Conclusion:

The sender domain attempts to impersonate a financial institution using urgency and fear tactics. The email encourages users to verify account details through an external link. This email is classified as a phishing attempt.
